ARGUMENT.

Disdaining the court's or king's complainings, Fate has carried away Moray ere his time. After the removal of that star, Fullerton was drowned in Lethe’s untimely surge. Let Lachesis tage at will: after such sad deaths‚ nor court nor king can mourn.
